---
---

<section class="section features" id="hardware">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="eyebrow">HARDWARE //</div>
		<h2 class="section-title">Two nodes. One private AI cluster.</h2>
		<p class="section-lede">
			Claw runs OpenClaw agents. Crush runs local LLMs via Ollama with CUDA.
			Together they form a complete, always-on inference system that fits
			on your desk.
		</p>

		<div class="grid">
			<article class="card card-blue">
				<div class="card-label">01 // CLUSTERCLAW</div>
				<h3>OpenClaw node</h3>
				<p>
					Raspberry Pi 5 (8 GB) running OpenClaw — the agent runtime.
					Handles planning, memory, tool dispatch, and MCP server
					coordination. 28 built-in MCP tools across five servers:
					LEDs, system, clustercrush bridge, time, and files.
				</p>
				<div class="spec-row">
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">SoC</span>RPi 5 BCM2712</div>
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">RAM</span>8 GB LPDDR4X</div>
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">Role</span>Agents / MCP</div>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="card card-red">
				<div class="card-label">02 // CLUSTERCRUSH</div>
				<h3>Local LLM inference node</h3>
				<p>
					Jetson Orin Nano Super (8 GB) with dedicated CUDA cores
					running Ollama. Serves models to Claw and to ThreadWeaver
					chat — no GPU sharing with your workstation.
				</p>
				<div class="spec-row">
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">SoC</span>Orin Nano Super</div>
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">RAM</span>8 GB unified</div>
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">Role</span>Ollama / CUDA</div>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="card card-amber">
				<div class="card-label">03 // LED FEEDBACK</div>
				<h3>Physical AI status strip</h3>
				<p>
					Pimoroni Blinkt! LED strip driven by an MCP server — the first
					MCP server for physical AI feedback. Claw's agents light the
					strip to reflect model state, inference activity, and alerts.
					Your AI is visible, not just running.
				</p>
				<div class="spec-row">
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">Type</span>Blinkt! RGB</div>
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">MCP</span>8 tools</div>
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">First</span>Physical MCP</div>
				</div>
			</article>

			<article class="card card-dim">
				<div class="card-label">04 // 28 MCP TOOLS</div>
				<h3>Agents that control the hardware</h3>
				<p>
					Five MCP servers expose every cluster capability to OpenClaw:
					LED strip animation, system metrics, LLM bridge to Crush,
					time/scheduling, and local file access. Agents use tools, not
					config files.
				</p>
				<div class="spec-row">
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">Servers</span>5</div>
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">Tools</span>28</div>
					<div class="spec"><span class="spec-label">Proto</span>MCP / stdio</div>
				</div>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.features {
		background:
			radial-gradient(
				ellipse 70% 40% at 50% 100%,
				rgba(27, 117, 186, 0.04),
				transparent 60%
			),
			var(--ctx-bg);
	}

	.eyebrow {
		display: inline-block;
		padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
		background: rgba(27, 117, 186, 0.08);
		border: 1px solid rgba(27, 117, 186, 0.28);
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.1em;
		color: var(--claw-blue-text);
		font-weight: 700;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 1.25rem;
		margin-top: 0.5rem;
	}

	.card {
		background: var(--ctx-panel);
		border: 1px solid var(--ctx-border);
		border-radius: var(--ctx-radius-lg);
		padding: 1.5rem;
		position: relative;
		overflow: hidden;
		transition: transform 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
	}

	.card::before {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		right: 0;
		height: 3px;
	}

	.card-blue::before {
		background: var(--claw-blue);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(27, 117, 186, 0.5);
	}

	.card-red::before {
		background: var(--claw-red);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(230, 57, 70, 0.5);
	}

	.card-amber::before {
		background: var(--ctx-warn);
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(252, 211, 77, 0.4);
	}

	.card-dim::before {
		background: var(--ctx-border-hi);
	}

	.card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-2px);
		box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
	}

	.card-label {
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
		font-size: 0.68rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.12em;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.card-blue .card-label { color: var(--claw-blue-text); }
	.card-red .card-label { color: var(--claw-red-text); }
	.card-amber .card-label { color: var(--ctx-warn); }
	.card-dim .card-label { color: var(--ctx-text-faint); }

	.card h3 {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0;
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		color: #ffffff;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.card p {
		color: var(--ctx-text-dim);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
		line-height: 1.55;
	}

	.spec-row {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1rem;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
	}

	.spec {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.15rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		color: #ffffff;
		font-family: var(--ctx-font-mono);
	}

	.spec-label {
		font-size: 0.65rem;
		color: var(--ctx-text-faint);
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
	}

	@media (max-width: 700px) {
		.grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
